<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Hardened runtime opt-ins. Empty dict = stock hardened runtime, which is what App Store /
        notarization require by default. Add exceptions here only when something actually breaks:
          - com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit       — if a future scripting/runtime needs JIT pages
          - com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory — JIT w/o the above
          - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation — load dylibs from outside the bundle
          - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables — DYLD_* for debugging
        SDL3 + Lua (interpreter, no JIT) + statically-linked deps don't need any of the above.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
